23/01/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska Prime Minister- designate Pero Bukejlovic said Friday (21 January) that he has managed to secure a majority support in parliament for the future government. He said will also try to obtain backing from the Party of Democratic Action, but ruled out their participation in the government. The opposition Alliance of Independent Social Democrats, meanwhile, has refused to hold talks with Bukejlovic. (FENA - 22/01/05; Republika Srpska TV - 21/01/05) 
